rComments: Interesting at times. Because the class is so discussion-oriented it is crucial to read over all texts prior to class. Homework assignments, however are rarely quick. Be prepared to sometimes dedicate an hour to one text. He does a good job of conceptualizing.

Do the readings before class - Keller explains well, but it helps to situate oneself. Daily homework, small writing assignments, 1-2 longer papers, in-class participation. Sometimes he uses PPT, movie clips, articles, etc to support learning. Emphasis on connections between people/events/perspectives, rather than facts/dates.

Pretty good class overall, pretty interesting lectures, hardly any graded assignments so do a good job on the ones there are - just 2 papers a midterm and a final. Other than that its just participation and daily homework on readings
